Text.string: Vault Hunter. I thought you might show up sooner or later. So naughty, your species. So curious. The Vault of Vaults has been opened... and it has been released. Prove your worth, and I will reveal why the Masters made me wait for you.
Naughty humans opened the Vault of Vaults, but the Masters will determine who is at fault. Until next time, “warrior”.

A final chance to prove yourself. But will your reward be what you desire? A prisoner in a cell staring out at the fathoms of a sleeping universe. After a time, how would you know whether you were prisoner or master? Consider this while you prove yourself one last time.

It is done, and my masters have taken note. Would you like to know what they told me right before they vanished? “Beware the Vault Hunters. They will take your kind's place.” Now I am free. And you are chained. Until next time... “guardian”.
It is time to prove yourself once again.
Some skill has been demonstrated, I suppose.
You do have SOME skills, I suppose.
Well done, but have they taken note? THAT is what I wonder.
Do you have more to prove?
Let us up the ante, shall we?
We have reached the trial's end.
A final battle to prove yourself.
A notable achievement, for your kind.
So, you've returned! Persistent, yes? Or stubborn. Or both! Are you so desperate to prove yourself? Then let us begin.
Long ago, there was a brief spark. The first Vault was opened, a light in the dark. A riddle, yes? Perhaps it will unravel next time, “hunter”.

We were created for one purpose by our masters—and we couldn't even do THAT right. [chuckles] But don't blame us! When a cog breaks, point your finger at the artificer, not the cog! Are you a cog, Vault Hunter, or an artificer? Or both? Prove yourself worthy.
Pity us not, though the world has been broken. Those who sleep will soon be awoken. Not long now, “seeker”.

The Eridians were our masters. But we failed them! They gave the order. Then silence. They vanished! Such is our fate, Vault Hunter. Servant to a master who has left the house so long ago. Prove to me that you deserve an introduction.
We were supposed to guard the great jail. But no quarter for servants who fail. But “servant”, that is not quite right. Prisoner. THAT is what I am. Until next time, “adventurer”.

I am a prisoner—but you, Vault Hunter? What are you? Hunter. Warrior. Hero. No matter what name I use, you return to prove yourself time and time again. But prove it to WHOM, I wonder. Perhaps you seek a greater audition?
It has come to this: one last trial. But will your efforts be worthwhile? THAT we will determine next time, “hero”.
